There are times when you want to keep the SQL code as general and short as possible. 
The next example shows how to write a generic SQL query where some conditions can be skipped by setting the parameter as null.
Consider a method that selects all persons that fulfill certain requirements.
To simplify the example, let's consider the requirements to be applied all at once, meaning that AND should be used.
